## 🔴 Critical Bugs (Extension Will Not Work)

### 1. Content script dependencies are not loaded

> [!CAUTION]
> This is a **show-stopper**. The extension will crash immediately on any supported page.

[manifest.json](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/manifest.json) only injects `content/content.js`:

```json
"content_scripts": [
  {
    "matches": ["https://www.hotstar.com/*"],
    "js": ["content/content.js"],
    "run_at": "document_start"
  }
]
```

But `content.js` calls `PlatformDetectors`, `Storage`, `API`, `Cache`, `Recommender`, and `Overlay` — **none of which are injected**. These are all separate files that are never loaded into the content script context.

**Fix required** — add all dependencies to the manifest:

```diff
 "content_scripts": [
   {
     "matches": ["https://www.hotstar.com/*"],
     "js": [
+      "utils/cache.js",
+      "utils/api.js",
+      "utils/storage.js",
+      "utils/recommender.js",
+      "content/platformDetectors.js",
+      "ui/overlay.js",
       "content/content.js"
     ],
-    "run_at": "document_start"
+    "run_at": "document_idle"
   }
 ]
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `run_at: "document_start"` is also wrong here — the content script queries DOM elements (`document.querySelector('h1')`) which don't exist yet at `document_start`. Change to `document_idle`.

---

### 2. Missing icon files — extension won't load

[manifest.json](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/manifest.json#L42-L46) references three icon PNGs:

```json
"icons": {
  "16": "assets/icons/icon-16.png",
  "48": "assets/icons/icon-48.png",
  "128": "assets/icons/icon-128.png"
}
```

The `assets/icons/` directory only contains a `README.md` — **no actual icon files exist**. Chrome will refuse to load the extension or show errors.

---

### 3. Missing `alarms` permission

[background.js:304](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/background/background.js#L304) uses `chrome.alarms.create()` but `"alarms"` is **not listed** in `manifest.json` permissions. This will throw a runtime error.

```diff
 "permissions": [
   "storage",
   "activeTab",
-  "scripting"
+  "scripting",
+  "alarms"
 ]
```

---

### 4. Background script references undefined globals

[background.js:90](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/background/background.js#L89-L95) calls `API.isConfigured()`, `API.BASE_URL`, and `API.TIMEOUT` — but the background service worker only loads `background.js`. The `API` object from `utils/api.js` is **never imported**.

MV3 service workers don't support `<script>` tags. You'd need `importScripts()`:

```js
// Top of background.js
importScripts('../utils/cache.js', '../utils/api.js', '../utils/storage.js');
```

---

## 🟠 Significant Code Issues

### 5. Wrong button reference in `resetAllData()`

In [popup.js:343-362](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/popup/popup.js#L337-L363), the `resetAllData()` function disables/re-labels `clearCacheBtn` instead of `resetAllBtn`:

```js
async function resetAllData() {
  clearCacheBtn.disabled = true;               // ← Wrong! Should be resetAllBtn
  clearCacheBtn.textContent = 'Resetting...';  // ← Wrong!
  // ...
  clearCacheBtn.textContent = 'Reset All Data'; // ← Wrong!
}
```

This means clicking "Reset All Data" disables the "Clear Cache" button and changes its label.

---

### 6. Genre tracking doesn't work for `searchMovie()` results

[api.js:90](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/utils/api.js#L90) stores `genre_ids` (integer arrays like `[28, 12]`) from the TMDb search endpoint:

```js
genres: movie.genre_ids || [],  // → [28, 12, 878]
```

But [storage.js:98](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/utils/storage.js#L97-L101) expects genre **objects** with `.name`:

```js
if (typeof genre === 'object' && genre.name) {
  genreCount[genre.name] = (genreCount[genre.name] || 0) + 1;
}
```

Since `genre_ids` are plain numbers (not objects), genres are **never counted** from the content script flow. The genre profile will always remain empty unless `getMovieDetails()` is called separately (which it currently isn't).

---

### 7. Duplicated logic across background.js and storage.js/cache.js

| Function | background.js | storage.js / cache.js |
|---|---|---|
| `getHistory()` | Lines 147-155 | `Storage.getHistory()` |
| `getBookmarks()` | Lines 161-169 | `Storage.getBookmarks()` |
| `exportUserData()` | Lines 175-197 | `Storage.exportData()` |
| `getCacheStats()` | Lines 203-232 | `Cache.getStats()` |
| `clearCache()` | Lines 238-257 | `Cache.clearAll()` |
| `trackMovieView()` | Lines 264-299 | `Storage.addToHistory()` |
| `getProfileSummary()` | Lines 113-141 | `Storage.getProfileSummary()` |

The background script **re-implements** nearly every function that already exists in the utility modules. This creates maintenance risk — if you fix a bug in one, the other stays broken.

---

### 8. `setupDynamicDetection()` is defined but never called

[content.js:235-255](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/content/content.js#L235-L255) — dead code. The function creates a `MutationObserver` but is never invoked anywhere.

---

### 9. `getMovieSpecificRecommendations()` uses wrong field names

[recommender.js:310-318](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/utils/recommender.js#L309-L318) maps fields as `poster_path` and `vote_average` from the raw API response, but `API.getSimilarMovies()` already normalizes to `posterPath` and `rating`. This means the returned objects will have `undefined` for poster and rating fields.

---

## 🟡 Code Quality & Design Concerns

### 10. API key hardcoded in source

[api.js:10](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/utils/api.js#L10) — Once a real key is added, it's fully visible in the extension source. Anyone who installs the extension can extract it. For a Chrome Web Store extension, consider a lightweight proxy server or at minimum storing in `chrome.storage.sync` with an options page.

### 11. No rate limiting on TMDb API calls

The recommender fetches similar movies for the last 3 history items + movies by top 3 genres = up to **6 API calls per recommendation request**, each potentially hitting TMDb. TMDb rate-limits at ~40 requests/10 seconds. Rapid navigation could cause 429 errors.

### 12. MutationObserver on `document.documentElement` is expensive

[platformDetectors.js:142-154](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/content/platformDetectors.js#L142-L154) — observes the **entire document** with `subtree: true` + `characterData: true`. On complex SPAs like Hotstar/Prime, this fires thousands of callbacks. Combined with the duplicate observer in `setupMovieDetection()`, this can cause noticeable performance degradation.

Consider debouncing callbacks or observing narrower DOM subtrees.

### 13. No input validation on import

[storage.js:344-364](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/utils/storage.js#L344-L364) — `importData()` trusts the backup object without validating structure, types, or sanitizing values. Malicious/corrupted backup files could inject arbitrary data into storage.

### 14. History dedup window too narrow

[storage.js:85](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/utils/storage.js#L85) — 60-second dedup window means the same movie gets re-added if the user stays on the page for over a minute (which is common). A better approach: dedup by `tmdbId` regardless of time.

### 15. Overlay card click does nothing

[overlay.js:300-307](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Documents/MY%20PROJECT/extension/movie-extension/ui/overlay.js#L300-L307) — clicking a movie card only logs to console. No navigation to the movie on TMDb or the streaming platform. This feels like an incomplete feature.

---

## ✅ What's Done Well

| Aspect | Assessment |
|---|---|
| **Code organization** | Clean module separation (API, Cache, Storage, Recommender, Overlay) |
| **Error handling** | Consistent try-catch with console logging throughout |
| **HTML escaping** | Proper XSS prevention via `_escapeHtml()` / `escapeHtml()` |
| **Fetch resilience** | Retry with exponential backoff + AbortController timeout |
| **Cache design** | TTL-based with automatic expiry cleanup via alarms |
| **UI/UX** | Dark theme, animations, skeleton loaders, keyboard shortcut (Alt+R) |
| **Accessibility** | `focus-visible` outlines, `aria-label` on buttons |
| **Privacy** | All data local, no external tracking |
| **Popup design** | Tab-based UI with settings modal is well-structured |

---

