## Verdict

> [!WARNING]
> The extension **will not work at all** in its current state. The 5 critical P0 issues (missing script injections, missing icons, missing permissions, missing imports in background) must be fixed before Chrome can even load and run it.

The underlying architecture and code patterns are solid — the module design, caching, and UI are well-thought-out. But the wiring between components (manifest configuration) is fundamentally broken. Once the P0/P1 items are addressed, this would be a functional, well-structured extension.

